genresAdvancedInfo.name: vietnamese traditional
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Vietnamese traditional music is a genre that has been passed down through generations. It includes a wide range of styles, from classical court music to folk songs and traditional opera. The music is often accompanied by traditional instruments such as the đàn tranh (a type of zither) and the đàn bầu (a one-stringed instrument). The genre is an important part of Vietnamese culture and history, and is often performed at festivals and other cultural events.
